{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489189","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489189"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:08:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:08:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"612"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/612"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.02,0.4,0.23,0.28]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"612"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81005"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"612","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/612"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"612"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66337"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1177"},{"type":"tags","id":"2047"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2770"},{"type":"tags","id":"3743"},{"type":"tags","id":"4965"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"6625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1959"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1974"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7497"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43022"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44256"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81005","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/81005"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 47-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a one-month history of fatigue and pallor noted by her husband. She has no weight loss, night sweats, pain, changes in bowel habits, or abdominal masses. She has a medical history of rheumatoid arthritis, migraine, and depression. Her medications include sertraline and methotrexate. She maintains a balanced diet including red meat three times weekly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears pale. Her pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 125/75 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. Her hands show swan-neck deformities and z-shaped thumbs. Abdominal examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHaemoglobin: 98 g/L (115-165)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMean cell volume: 85 fL (80-96)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhite cell count: 7.2 x 10^9/L (4.0-11.0)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPlatelet count: 250 x 10^9/L (150-400)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following patterns of iron studies would be most likely?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reduced serum iron, transferrin, and ferritin levels","Increased serum iron, transferrin, and ferritin levels","Reduced serum iron and transferrin levels, with increased ferritin","Reduced serum iron and ferritin, with increased serum transferrin levels","Normal iron studies"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with anaemia in the context of rheumatoid arthritis, a chronic inflammatory condition. The absence of blood loss, normal MCV, and well-balanced diet make iron deficiency anaemia less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced serum iron and transferrin levels, with increased ferritin\u003C/strong\u003E is the characteristic pattern seen in anaemia of chronic disease. This occurs due to inflammatory cytokines (particularly IL-6) increasing hepcidin production, which blocks iron release from storage by internalizing the iron transporter ferroportin. This leads to functional iron deficiency despite adequate iron stores.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced serum iron, transferrin, and ferritin levels\u003C/strong\u003E is the pattern seen in iron deficiency anaemia, which is unlikely given the patient\u0027s adequate dietary intake and absence of blood loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased serum iron, transferrin, and ferritin levels\u003C/strong\u003E is not a physiologically consistent pattern and would not explain the patient\u0027s anaemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced serum iron and ferritin, with increased serum transferrin levels\u003C/strong\u003E is the pattern seen in early iron deficiency, where the body attempts to compensate by increasing iron-binding capacity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal iron studies\u003C/strong\u003E would not be expected given the presence of significant anaemia in the context of chronic inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key to understanding this pattern is recognizing that inflammatory conditions like rheumatoid arthritis cause a functional iron deficiency through altered iron trafficking, rather than a true iron deficiency from inadequate stores or intake.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Anaemia of chronic disease is characterized by reduced serum iron and transferrin with increased ferritin levels due to inflammatory-mediated hepcidin upregulation.","Chronic inflammatory conditions like rheumatoid arthritis commonly cause anaemia of chronic disease through impaired iron utilization rather than iron deficiency.","The presence of normal MCV with anaemia in chronic inflammatory conditions suggests anaemia of chronic disease rather than iron deficiency anaemia."],"references":["Pagani A, Nai A, Silvestri L, Camaschella C. Hepcidin and Anemia: A Tight Relationship. Front Physiol. 2019 Oct 9;10:1294. doi: 10.3389/fphys.2019.01294. PMID: 31649559; PMCID: PMC6794341.","Pasricha SR, Flecknoe-Brown SC, Allen KJ, Gibson PR, McMahon LP, Olynyk JK, Roger SD, Savoia HF, Tampi R, Thomson AR, Wood EM, Robinson KL. Diagnosis and management of iron deficiency anaemia: a clinical update. Med J Aust. 2010 Nov 1;193(9):525-32. doi: 10.5694/j.1326-5377.2010.tb04038.x. PMID: 21034387.","de Las Cuevas Allende R, D\u00edaz de Entresotos L, Conde D\u00edez S. Anaemia of chronic diseases: Pathophysiology, diagnosis and treatment. Anemia de las enfermedades cr\u00f3nicas: fisiopatolog\u00eda, diagn\u00f3stico y tratamiento. Med Clin (Barc). 2021;156(5):235-242. doi:10.1016/j.medcli.2020.07.035"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66337"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"612"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66337","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66337"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-24T21:13:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-24T21:13:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"612"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81005"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"t